OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1776767959
OL,3,CGraveyards being made safer after
OL,4,Cdeath of young boy
OL,6,FA spokesperson said: "The initial
OL,7,Fstage of work has involved inspecting
OL,8,Fmemorials and making them temporarily
OL,9,Fsafe for visitors. Now, we have
OL,10,Fcommenced the next phase of work,
OL,11,Fwhich focuses on making memorials
OL,12,Fpermanently safe.
OL,14,F"This may include setting stones
OL,15,Fupright, laying them flat or levelling
OL,16,Fthe surrounding ground to improve
OL,17,Faccessibility, while keeping
OL,18,Finscriptions visible wherever possible.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/4
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,392,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F391A1776767959
OL,3,CGraveyards being made safer after
OL,4,Cdeath of young boy
OL,6,F"This work represents an important
OL,7,Fstep in ensuring safer and more-
OL,8,Fwelcoming cemeteries for everyone
OL,9,Fvisiting loved ones."
OL,11,FThe council said if a memorial needs
OL,12,Fattention, relatives should use an
OL,13,Fapproved stonemason and not try to
OL,14,Frepair it themselves.
OL,16,FA permit is required to carry out
OL,17,Fwork, but will be provided free of
OL,18,Fcharge for repairs identified during
OL,19,Fthe safety inspection process, the
OL,20,Fcouncil said.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/4
